cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.CY

The paper proposes a deep neural network-based learning framework for accurate classification of motor imagery EEG signals for Brain Computer Interface (BCI) applications. This involves interpreting EEG signals to interact with devices such as wheelchairs and intelligent robots. The paper focuses on the development of a BCI system for typing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a novel deep neural network-based learning framework. The paper also involves the use of Autoencoder layer to eliminate various artifacts such as background activities, which suggests the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of EEG signals to interpret human intent, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the development of a practical BCI system for typing, which suggests the category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of EEG signals to interact with devices such as wheelchairs and intelligent robots, which suggests the category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
